  "body": "# Bug Report\r\nThe checkbox from terms and condition initial screen inside the app has not enough color contrast and users using the mobile with lower lightning rate are not able to see this, getting block into the screen unless they tap on it by instinct.\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n[comment]: # (A problem description)\r\n  Users cannot see the checkbox from terms and condition to move forward.\r\n  \r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nChange checkbox color contrast to at least 4.5:1 ratio so users can see it clearly and move forward into the app.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nColor contrast lower than 4:5:1 ration so users cannot see unless they have the lightning rate at max.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Put your device screen lightning medium to low\r\n2. open the app for the first time > users cant see the checkbox b/c the lower contrast ration with the background vs checkbox color.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n https://accessibleweb.com/color-contrast-checker/\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS - both.\r\n\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Please, add logs/notes if necessary)\r\n\r\n",
